 So, the thing about going in the deep end is you actually have to let yourself go in the

00:02:14.740 --> 00:02:40.100
 deep end.

00:02:40.100 --> 00:02:47.100
 And that's how we get free.

00:02:47.100 --> 00:02:58.700
 The dhamma is so deep and it's so, it's so kind.

00:02:58.700 --> 00:03:13.900
 The nature is so kind. Tara is so kind. Our teachers are so kind.

00:03:13.900 --> 00:03:32.380
 They're not going to force us to do anything. They're going to say, "Here's the next step.

00:03:32.380 --> 00:03:42.300
 The big door." And it's completely up to us to keep going. And that's what a healthy

00:03:42.300 --> 00:03:48.900
 lineage does. And that's what a healthy teacher-student relationship empowers. And that's who our

00:03:48.900 --> 00:03:49.180
 kind

00:03:49.180 --> 00:04:08.940
 of teachers are. We have everything. We don't need all of interdependence to understand

00:04:08.940 --> 00:04:23.460
 interdependence. We need a clear, reliable way to take the next step, to just let Tara

00:04:23.460 --> 00:04:37.300
 be Tara. Let ourselves be ourselves. Let the nature do what the nature does. And it's totally

00:04:37.300 --> 00:04:48.300
 up to us. It is totally up to us. And it's always been like that. And maybe this time,

00:04:48.300 --> 00:05:02.040
 maybe this time, we can really bravely, beautifully, powerfully, humbly, really let ourselves m

